<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Spektor Ironhide</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-22 01:50:23</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Erm... To the post above, 2 FBSS in 5 mins? Are you on crack or something? Lower Guk has a 30 minute spawn time, and only one Frenzied can spawn in that 30 minutes.. I camped the frenzied/sent spawned today for about 3 or 4 hours with the following group:  35 Cleric, 48 Ench, 43 War, 40 War (me), 40 War, and 48 Necro.  Spawn gave us no trouble what so ever and the exp was great.  I scored about 1.2 bubbles in 40 hell level.  In the 4 hours, one Frenzied Ghoul spawned, and luckily he dropped the FBSS. Being the only tank in the group without one, i was the recipient of the sash.  At first glance i noticed no visual difference in the speed of my slashing and was kind of dissapointed.  Later i fought some shin knights and experimented taking sash off in middle of fight.  There was a noticable difference in speed... probably about 15%-20% increase with sash on.  There is no proc or anything, its permanent haste.  Group was 35-48, and we had no issues.  Definatley a great tank tool!<BR>
<BR>
Spektor Ironhide<BR>
40th Warrior, Vallon Zek<BR>
Black Sun</font></td></tr></table>
