<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Kasane</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-12 09:23:34</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Why hello there...I see an awful lot of posts here and most of them seem pretty useless. Well I come to do my part in the philosophey of "Community". <BR>
<BR>
Iv'e always been curious as to what my weapons damage per second was after I equipped the FBSS/RBB, so I figured out a simple formula you can do on a calculator in about 10 seconds.<BR>
<BR>
Here goes Pay attentoin!<BR>
<BR>
-Find the weapons origonal DELAY-<BR>
<BR>
-Take that number and MULTIPLY that by the haste percentage-<BR>
<BR>
-To multiply a percentage simply put one DECIMAL before the number of the percentage-<BR>
<BR>
Example: "The FBSS has a 25% Haste effect" So multiply the weapons delay by 0.25<BR>
<BR>
-Take your result and subtract that from the ORIGONAL delay on the weapon-<BR>
<BR>
Example: 40 Delay MULTIPLIED by 25% equals TEN. 40 Minus 10 equals THIRTY. Making the weapon with a haste belt now a THIRTY delay.<BR>
<BR>
Now you shuold have a fairly accurate Damage/delay ratio when applying this method. But you want to know the new damage per/second right?<BR>
<BR>
Good your so enthusiastic!<BR>
<BR>
Go to the Mithril 2-hander page and see my damage per second formula!<BR>
<BR>
-Kasane Vivandiere-<BR>
28th level warrior-<BR>
Bristlebane</font></td></tr></table>
